        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(agents): expose estimated context budget status",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nExpose OpenClaw's pre-prompt context budget estimate when fresh provider usage is unavailable.\n\n- capture a typed, path-free `contextBudgetStatus` snapshot from the pre-prompt estimate\n- persist that snapshot on `SessionEntry`\n- expose it on gateway session rows\n- let `/status` show estimated context usage only when fresh provider usage is unavailable or absent\n- keep positive fresh `totalTokens` authoritative\n- prevent preserved-runtime heartbeat runs from replacing the main session's budget snapshot\n- reserve the new top-level session field from plugin session-entry slot mirroring\n\nThis is reporting-only. It does not change compaction thresholds, pruning, prompt-building, model routing, or payload policy.\n\nRefs #80594, #54996, #77992, #84490, #83177, #43009, #83526, #8635.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `git diff --check refs/remotes/openclaw/main...HEAD`\n- `.\\node_modules\\.bin\\oxfmt.CMD --check src/config/sessions/types.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/preemptive-compaction.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/preemptive-compaction.test.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/attempt.ts src/gateway/session-utils.types.ts src/gateway/session-utils.ts src/gateway/session-utils.test.ts`\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 OPENCLAW_VITEST_FS_MODULE_CACHE_PATH=.artifacts/vitest-cache/budget2-gateway-row-simple node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/session-utils.test.ts -t \"session rows expose estimated context budget status\" --reporter=verbose`\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 OPENCLAW_VITEST_FS_MODULE_CACHE_PATH=.artifacts/vitest-cache/budget2-preemptive-simple-rerun node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/preemptive-compaction.test.ts --reporter=verbose`\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 OPENCLAW_VITEST_FS_MODULE_CACHE_PATH=.artifacts/vitest-cache/budget2-session-store-simple node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/command/session-store.test.ts -t \"heartbeat bleed fix\" --reporter=verbose`\n- `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.core.test.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/budget2-core-test-simple.tsbuildinfo`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Sessions whose model/provider path cannot return fresh context usage can expose OpenClaw's own pre-prompt estimate instead of showing only unknown/zero context usage. Preserved-runtime heartbeat runs cannot overwrite the main session's budget snapshot.\n\nReal environment tested: Windows isolated worktree on PR head `4911102b66`, with local dependencies installed.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: the verification commands listed above.\n\nEvidence after fix: The preemptive-compaction tests passed in `agents-core` and `agents-pi-embedded`, proving the durable estimate snapshot is built from the pre-prompt decision. The gateway-row regression passed in `gateway-core`, `gateway-server`, and `gateway-client`, proving session rows expose the estimated budget status. The heartbeat regression passed in `agents-core` and `agents-support`, proving preserved-runtime heartbeat updates keep the existing Anthropic model/window and budget snapshot.\n\nObserved result after fix: `contextBudgetStatus` is a path-free status object with provider, model, route, estimate, budget, reserve, overflow, message counts, and optional `sessionId`; `/status` can use it as an estimated fallback when fresh usage is absent.\n\nWhat was not tested: Full Vitest files, broad `pnpm check:changed`, and a live provider-backed `/status` run were not rerun locally.\r\n",
        "branch": "budget-2-context-budget-status",
